<title>BRAZIL: Brazil 1997 privatizations make $16.57 bln - Kandir.</title>
<headline>Brazil 1997 privatizations make $16.57 bln - Kandir.</headline>
<dateline>BRASILIA 1997-08-14</dateline>
<text>
<p>Brazil's federal government and its states have made $16.57 billion through asset sales this year, 90 percent of total privatization receipts in the preceeding seven years, Planning Minister Antonio Kandir said.</p>
<p>Kandir told reporters the figure included $13 billion in assets up to July, with the rest representing gains through retiring debt and transferring debt from the public sector to the private sector.</p>
<p>&quot;It's surpassed all expectations,&quot; Kandir said. The government's original target for privatization receipts in 1997 was $10 billion.</p>
